tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  28,60,"Whatever thing you have been given is the enjoyment of the present life and its adornment; and what is with God is better and more enduring."
  28,68,"Thy Lord creates whatsoever He will and He chooses; they have not the choice. Glory be to God! High be He exalted above that they associate!"
  28,69,"And thy Lord knows what their breasts conceal and what they publish."